CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 30, 1945, pg. 13, reads: "Talking it Over - Gov. Edward Martin, himself a retired general, chats with Generals Devers and Joseph T. McNarney, and Lieut. Gen. William H. Simpson as they stepped off their planes at the County Airport Monday...then the parade before 100,000 spectators. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Pennsylvania Governor Edward Martin, General Joseph T. McNarney, General Jacob L. Devers, and Lieut. General William H. Simpson at Allegheny County airport with county police motorcycles in background
